If a constitutional corporation owns a disclosure affected building, the corporation must not do any of the following unless a valid, current building energy efficiency certificate for the building is registered:
* offer, or continue to offer, to sell the building;
* invite offers, or continue to invite offers, to purchase the building;
* offer, or continue to offer, to let the building;
* invite offers, or continue to invite offers, to lease the building.
* invite offers, or continue to invite offers, to lease the building.
 Civil penalty: 1,000 penalty units.
* offer, or continue to offer, to sublet the building;
* invite offers, or continue to invite offers, to sublease the building.

